   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_696_1818-10-29_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Harley-Street-31_ENK"/>31 Harley S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                  <date when="1818-10-29">29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> <choice><orig>Octo<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></orig><reg>October</reg></choice> 1818</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                My dearest <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">mother</persName> - We have spent two<lb/>
                days &amp; half in Town sleeping at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Harley-Street-31_ENK">Harley S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</placeName>
               <lb/>
                and at every other moment that we could<lb/>
                spare from <hi rend="underline">business</hi> with dear kind <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>.<lb/>
                Marcet</persName> - she had two <add>bed</add> rooms opening<lb/>
                into each other prepared for us &amp; w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. hard<lb/>
                by permit us to sleep any where else -<lb/>
                — We have been as busy as possible — <unclear>In</unclear>
               <lb/>
                morning I went to the Charter House with<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL2">Mr. L W</persName>— <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RussJ2">Mr. Russell</persName> exceedingly obliging<lb/>
                — a very gentle sedate sensible man —<lb/>
                inquired for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL2">Lovell</persName> kindly — shewed us all<lb/>
                the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Charter-House_ENK">Charter House</placeName> — fine play ground —<lb/>
                recommended a boarding house now<lb/>
                repairing for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF2">Francis</persName> — <add>will</add> put him under<lb/>
                the care of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeddT1">Tom Beddoes</persName> — Each Boarding<lb/>
                house has a monitor answerable for<lb/>
                a certain number — we saw <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeddT1">Tom</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#XxxxH1">Henry</persName>
               <lb/>
                — they look forward to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF2">Francis's</persName> coming<lb/>
                with pleasure — <del>From</del> All I saw &amp;<lb/>
                heard convinced me that it is wise to<lb/>
                send <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF2">Francis</persName> to this school — I mean<lb/>
                all I saw of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RussJ2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Russell</persName> — as to the rest<lb/>
                I could know nothing but that bed <choice>
                  <orig>cham<lb/>
                ers</orig>
                  <reg>chambers</reg>
               </choice> &amp; play ground are good — <lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I took the decided step of putting<lb/>
                his name on the list — There will be<lb/>
                a vacancy <add>at xmas</add> the 2n<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Wednesday in Jan<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_696_1818-10-29_page02.jpg"/>

                is I think the day when he should be at<lb/>
                the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Charter-House_ENK">Charter House</placeName> — I have written it down<lb/>
                with other particulars but have not now<lb/>
                time look for the paper — I will send in<lb/>
                next packet<lb/> —</p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora's</persName> teeth have been filed &amp; cleaned<lb/>
                by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WaitX1">Waite</persName> — a great coxcomb — but a<lb/>
                good dentist — cost £5 —<lb/>
                F &amp; she persuaded me to let Alexander<lb/>
                see my eyes - He says there is no danger<lb/>
                of my losing them - that all I feel<lb/>
                proceeds from having overstrained<lb/>
                them this has <unclear>bt</unclear> on a disease in the<lb/>
                absorbent <unclear>vessels</unclear> of lids - he has given<lb/>
                an ointment I fancy same as yours.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I enclose a list of places we went<lb/>
                to yesterday morning - Good <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Marcet</persName>
               <lb/>
                assisted us in the preceding evening to<lb/>
                make out the right order of the streets<lb/>
                - We had an ex<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. coachman &amp; <unclear>job</unclear>
               <lb/>
                chariot while our own was repairing<lb/>
                - no difficulties - And I really was<lb/>
                so busy that I had not time to <hi rend="underline">feel</hi>
               <lb/>
                all I thought I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> in going about by<lb/>
               <del>myself</del> without you -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <del>This morn</del>Yesterday at <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Marcets</persName>
               <lb/>
               <add>dined</add>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WishX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
               </persName> - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SebrJ1">T. John Seebright</persName> - &amp; <unclear>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ProoX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>Proofs</persName>
               </unclear>
               <lb/>
                - Eve &amp; <persName ref="./Persography.xml#MallX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi>
               </persName> &amp; <hi rend="underline&gt;">new</hi>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MallX2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Mallet</persName> - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WollW1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Wollaston</persName>
               <lb/>
                the preceding day -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcA1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Marcet</persName> gave us introduction<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_696_1818-10-29_page03.jpg"/>

                to museum this morning &amp; we went<lb/>
                with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Marcet</persName> &amp; a party to see the<lb/>
                Phyalian &amp; Elgin marbles - and all<lb/>
                you &amp; I saw before in the museum -<lb/>
                we had the pleaseure of taking <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. L W</persName>&amp;<lb/>
                his brother with us -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora</persName> was pleased but had scarcely<lb/>
                time to see or enjoy 1/00000th. part<lb/>
                - <persName ref="personography.xml#SmitX2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Smith</persName> one of the <hi rend="underline">orderers</hi> of Museum<lb/>
                amazingly civil - shewed <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora</persName>
               <lb/>
                the fine volumes of Rembrandts<lb/>
                &amp; Antonios - prints<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> We went from Museum to call<lb/>
                on <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GrifX3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Griffiths</persName> - returned to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Harley-Street-31_ENK"/>Harley S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
               <lb/>
                to take up baggage - I write this while<lb/>
                the trunks are putting on -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> We shall call to see <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AngeX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Angersteins</persName>
               <lb/>
                pictures <add>as we go to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Kensington-Gore_ENK">Kensington</placeName>
               </add> for which I have a tiket<lb/>
                - Then to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WhitE1">Lady E W</persName> - to dinner - sleep<lb/>
                there - &amp; to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Wimbledon_ENK">Wimbledon</placeName> next day to<lb/>
                dinner - stay till 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. spend but<lb/>
               one day at <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HopeX3">the Hopes</persName> because yes<lb/>
                terday I rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> a letter from M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. D S - <choice>
                  <orig>say<lb/>
                ing</orig>
                  <reg>saying</reg>
               </choice> they will be at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Bowood-House_ENK">Bowood</placeName> on the<lb/>
                3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> Now the purpose for which I<lb/>
                got this frank was to send you patterns<lb/>
                of cloth I obtained yesterday from <unclear>Otley</unclear>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_696_1818-10-29_page04.jpg"/>
            <p> - There is no black <hi rend="underline">Vigonia</hi> the vigonia<lb/>
                wool will not take black dye.<lb/>
                Tell me which you prefer the merino<lb/>
                or the Queens cloth - the prices &amp;<lb/>
                width you will see - The Queens cloth<lb/>
                comes to a guinea <add>the dress</add> cheaper <lb/>- -
                - The merino looks much the best in<lb/>
                the piece - Otley will send it to me<lb/>
                when I know your decision<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> Poor <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsB1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Wilson</persName> is so weak that I<lb/>
                think she cannot last long - She does<lb/>
                not seem to suffer much -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I have not yet rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> your packet<lb/>
                mentioned in your last letter as sent<lb/>
                by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ConnX1">Connor</persName> &amp; am in great impatience<lb/>
                for it - My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Fanny's</persName> letter to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora</persName> - rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> yesterday &amp; swallowed<lb/>
                in the carriage - I fear she has never<lb/>
                received one from me<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                Your affec<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria E</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back> </back>
